# ============================================================================
# CivicTwin — AI Coding Rules
# Bharatiya Antariksh Hackathon 2026
# Team: CivicTwin | Leader: Guru Venkata Krishna Egiti, VIT-AP University
# Pilot City: Hyderabad
# ============================================================================

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. ARCHITECTURE — DECOUPLED, ZERO-COST FREE TIERS
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Frontend : React + Deck.gl + MapLibre GL JS → deployed on Vercel (free tier)
# Backend  : FastAPI (async) → deployed on Render (free tier)
# ML Infer : Dockerised FastAPI + TorchScript → Hugging Face Spaces (free tier)
# Database : Supabase PostgreSQL + PostGIS (free tier, 500 MB limit)
#
# Rule: The frontend NEVER bundles PyTorch, TensorFlow, or any heavy ML lib.
# Rule: The backend NEVER imports torch. It proxies inference requests to
#       the Hugging Face Space endpoint via httpx (async).
# Rule: All PINN / ML code lives exclusively in the `ml/` directory.
# Rule: Export trained models as TorchScript (.pt) for HF Space deployment.

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. FREE-TIER CONSTRAINTS — ALWAYS RESPECT
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Supabase : 500 MB storage, 2 GB bandwidth/month, 50k auth MAU
# Vercel   : No serverless functions in free tier; frontend is static SPA only
# HF Spaces: 2 vCPU, 16 GB RAM, no GPU on free tier
# Render   : 750 hrs/month free, sleeps after 15 min inactivity
#
# Rule: Never store large rasters in Supabase. Use COG on external storage.
# Rule: Keep Docker images lean — multi-stage builds, slim base images.

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 3. BACKEND — FastAPI on Render
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Language  : Python 3.11+
# Framework : FastAPI with async/await throughout (no sync endpoints)
# ORM       : SQLAlchemy 2.0+ async sessions with GeoAlchemy2 for PostGIS
# HTTP      : httpx (async) — prefer over requests in all cases
# Settings  : pydantic-settings (BaseSettings). NEVER hardcode secrets or URLs.
# Migrations: Alembic for schema evolution
# Linting   : Ruff (format + lint)
#
# Rule: NEVER use raw SQL strings in Python. All queries go through
#       SQLAlchemy ORM / Core with GeoAlchemy2 spatial functions.
# Rule: PostGIS spatial queries MUST use ST_* functions via GeoAlchemy2
#       (e.g., ST_Within, ST_DWithin, ST_Transform, ST_Area).
# Rule: API versioning — all routes under /api/v1/ prefix.
# Rule: CORS — allow Vercel production domain AND http://localhost:5173.
# Rule: Use gradio_client or httpx to call the HF Space inference endpoint.
# Rule: ETL scripts live in `etl/` and share the backend Python environment.

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 4. FRONTEND — React on Vercel
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Runtime   : Node 20+, TypeScript strict mode (strict: true in tsconfig)
# State     : Zustand (no Redux, no Context API for global state)
# HTTP      : Axios with interceptors for auth & error handling
# Map       : Deck.gl + MapLibre GL JS (open-source, no Mapbox token needed)
# Styling   : Tailwind CSS or CSS Modules — no inline styles in components
# Linting   : ESLint + Prettier
# Build     : Vite
#
# Rule: The frontend is a STATIC SPA. No server-side rendering, no API routes.
# Rule: All data fetching goes through the FastAPI backend, never direct DB.
# Rule: Map tiles via free providers (Carto, Stadia, OpenFreeMap).

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 5. ML / PINN — Hugging Face Spaces
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Location  : All model code in `ml/` directory only
# Framework : PyTorch (TorchScript for serving)
# Serving   : Dockerised FastAPI app deployed as HF Space (Docker SDK)
# Export    : torch.jit.script or torch.jit.trace → .pt files
#
# Rule: NEVER import torch outside of `ml/` or the HF Space container.
# Rule: Model artifacts (.pt files) are stored in the HF Space repo, not in
#       the backend or Supabase.
# Rule: The backend calls the HF Space via its public URL using httpx.

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 6. DATABASE — Supabase PostGIS
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Engine    : PostgreSQL 15+ with PostGIS extension
# ORM layer : SQLAlchemy 2.0 + GeoAlchemy2
# Async     : asyncpg driver for async sessions
# Migrations: SQL files in `infra/supabase/migrations/`
#
# Rule: Enable PostGIS extension before creating spatial tables.
# Rule: All geometry columns MUST have SRID 4326 (WGS 84).
# Rule: Create GIST indices on every geometry column.
# Rule: Use gen_random_uuid() for UUID primary key defaults.
# Rule: JSONB for flexible properties — validate shape in application layer.

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 7. DATA FORMATS
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Rasters : Cloud-Optimised GeoTIFF (COG) — rio-cogeo for conversion
# Vectors : GeoJSON (RFC 7946) for API responses
# Internal: WKB via GeoAlchemy2 for DB storage
#
# Rule: Never store raw GeoTIFF blobs in Supabase. Reference external URLs.

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 8. CI/CD — GitHub Actions
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Python CI : Ruff lint + pytest on every PR
# TS CI     : ESLint + vitest on every PR
# Deploy    : Auto-deploy frontend to Vercel via GitHub integration
# Deploy    : Auto-deploy backend to Render via GitHub integration
# Deploy    : Auto-deploy ML space to HF via `huggingface_hub` CLI
#
# Rule: All secrets in GitHub Actions secrets, never in code or .env committed.
# Rule: .env files are .gitignored. Use .env.example as a template.

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 9. PROJECT STRUCTURE (reference)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# civictwin/
# ├── frontend/          # React + Deck.gl (Vercel)
# ├── backend/           # FastAPI (Render)
# ├── ml/                # PINN models + TorchScript export
# ├── etl/               # Data ingestion scripts (shared backend env)
# ├── infra/             # Supabase migrations, Docker, IaC
# │   └── supabase/
# │       └── migrations/
# ├── .github/workflows/ # CI/CD
# ├── .cursorrules       # This file
# └── pyproject.toml     # Python project metadata
